  "body": "Was using LG Nexus\n\n**Enter your pairing code screen**\n\n- The layout is wrong in many places here: margins, text alignment, error placement;\n\n<img width=\"944\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2019-10-14 at 12 16 05\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/66740959-0db81000-ee7d-11e9-8699-2f599bee0333.png\">\n\n- I somehow ended up on this screen with no keyboard opened. To open it i had to tap randomly since the text input is invisible. It should be impossible to hide a keyboard on such screens;\n\n**Recover with seed phrase screen**\n- The layout is broken + I can't see the seed phrase I've entered;\n![photo_2019-10-14 12 20 16](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/66740937-ff69f400-ee7c-11e9-83ec-b94bb8f252cb.jpeg)\n\n- After I successfully recovered an account I see an infinite \"Welcome to status\" screen. I can stop it from spinning by tapping the phone's OS \"back\" button and then I see the chat screen with an endless spinner replacing the \"+\" button;",
